items.title: Ashok Leyland Q1 Results: Net profit jumps 13% to Rs 594 crore; revenue up 1.5%
items.description: Ashok Leyland posted a standalone net profit of Rs 593.73 crore for Q1 FY26, up 13% YoY, on revenue of Rs 8,724.51 crore, a 1.5% rise. Consolidated net profit attributable to owners rose 20% YoY to Rs 611.07 crore. The company saw record Q1 commercial vehicle volumes, improved margins, and strong contributions from core and export businesses.
